2026-06-01 | Maximum Product Subset of an Array

Question
Return maximum product possible from any subset.
	Key Insight
To maximize product:
1. Include all positive numbers.
2. Include negative numbers in pairs.
3. If count of negative numbers is odd:
		remove the negative number
		with smallest absolute value
		(largest value among negatives).
4. Zeros are useful only when product
		would otherwise be negative.
	Approach
1. Count:
		negatives
		zeros
2. Find negative having maximum value
		(e.g. -1 preferred over -5)
3. Multiply all non-zero elements.
4. If negatives count is odd:
		divide product by removed negative.
5. Handle special cases:
		only zeros
		single negative with zeros
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    long long maxProductSubset(vector<int>& arr) {
        const long long MOD = 1000000007;
        int n = arr.size();
        if(n == 1){
            long long x = arr[0];
            x %= MOD;
            if(x < 0) x += MOD;
            return x;
        }
        long long product = 1;
        int negCount = 0;
        int zeroCount = 0;
        int maxNegative = INT_MIN;
        for(int x : arr){
            if(x == 0){
                zeroCount++;
                continue;
            }
            if(x < 0){
                negCount++;
                maxNegative = max(maxNegative, x);
            }
            product *= x;
        }
        // all zeros
        if(zeroCount == n)
            return 0;
        // only one negative and rest zeros
        if(negCount == 1 &&
           zeroCount + negCount == n)
            return 0;
        if(negCount & 1){
            product /= maxNegative;
        }
        product %= MOD;
        if(product < 0)
            product += MOD;
        return product;
    }
};
	Key Insight
A negative product is harmful when we can avoid it.
If the number of negatives is odd,
remove the negative whose absolute value is smallest
(the negative closest to zero).
This keeps the final positive product as large as possible.
